    "## Solutions to L'Hôpital's Rule Exercises",
    "",
    "### Exercise 1: L'Hôpital's Rule - 0/0 Form",
    "",
    "**a)** Yes",
    "",
    "**b)** lim (cos x)/1 = 1",
    "",
    "**c)** lim (sin x)/(2x) = lim (cos x)/2 = 1/2",
    "",
    "**d)** lim (3x²)/1 = 3",
    "",
    "**e)** lim (e^x)/1 = 1",
    "",
    "### Exercise 2: L'Hôpital's Rule - ∞/∞ Form",
    "",
    "**a)** lim (1)/e^x = 0",
    "",
    "**b)** lim (1/x)/1 = 0",
    "",
    "**c)** lim (1/x)/(-1/x²) = -x = -∞",
    "",
    "**d)** lim (2x)/e^x = 0",
    "",
    "**e)** lim (2x)/e^x = 0",
    "",
    "### Exercise 3: L'Hôpital's Rule - 0 × ∞ Form",
    "",
    "**a)** Yes",
    "",
    "**b)** lim x ln x = lim ln x / (1/x) = lim (1/x) / (-1/x²) = lim -x = 0",
    "",
    "**c)** lim x / e^x = 0",
    "",
    "**d)** lim x cot x = lim x (cos x / sin x) = lim (cos x / sin x) + x (-sin x / sin² x) wait, better: lim x / tan x = lim x cos x / sin x = lim cos x / (sin x / x) = 1/1 = 1",
    "",
    "**e)** lim √x / ln x = ∞",
    "",
    "### Exercise 4: L'Hôpital's Rule - ∞ - ∞ Form",
    "",
    "**a)** Yes",
    "",
    "**b)** lim (1 - 1/x) = 1",
    "",
    "**c)** lim (1/x - 1/sin x) = lim (-1/x² + cos x / sin² x) = lim (-1/x² + cot x csc x), apply again: lim (2/x³ + ...) = ∞",
    "",
    "**d)** lim (e^x - 1) = ∞",
    "",
    "**e)** lim (cot x - 1/x) = lim (-csc² x + 1/x²), set to 0: x = √(csc² x), but better approach needed",
    "",
    "### Exercise 5: L'Hôpital's Rule - 0⁰, ∞⁰, 1^∞ Forms",
    "",
    "**a)** Yes",
    "",
    "**b)** ln y = x ln x, lim = 0, so y = 1",
    "",
    "**c)** ln y = x ln(1 + 1/x) = x (1/x - 1/(2x²) + ...) = 1 - 1/(2x) + ..., lim = 1, y = e",
    "",
    "**d)** ln y = x ln sin x, lim_{x→0} = 0, y = 1",
    "",
    "**e)** ln y = x ln(1 + a/x) = x (a/x - a²/(2x²) + ...) = a - a²/(2x) + ..., lim = a, y = e^a",
    "",
    "### Exercise 6: L'Hôpital's Rule - Multiple Applications",
    "",
    "**a)** lim (sin x)/(2x) = 1/2",
    "",
    "**b)** lim (e^x - 1)/ (2x) = 1/2",
    "",
    "**c)** lim (cos x - 1)/(-6x²) wait, first: lim (sin x - 1)/ (3x²) = lim (cos x)/(6x) = lim (cos x)/(6) = 1/6",
    "",
    "**d)** lim (2x - 2)/(2x + 3) = 1",
    "",
    "**e)** lim (2x - 2)/(2x + 3) = 1",
    "",
    "### Exercise 7: L'Hôpital's Rule with Trigonometric Functions",
    "",
    "**a)** lim (sec² x)/1 = 1",
    "",
    "**b)** lim (2 cos 2x)/3 = 2/3",
    "",
    "**c)** lim (sec² x)/1 = 1",
    "",
    "**d)** lim (2 sin 2x)/(2x) = lim (2 cos 2x)/2 = cos 0 = 1",
    "",
    "**e)** lim (cos x - sec² x)/(3x²) = lim (-sin x - 2 sec² x tan x)/ (6x) = 0/0 again, apply again",
    "",
    "### Exercise 8: L'Hôpital's Rule with Exponential Functions",
    "",
    "**a)** lim (1/x)/1 = 0",
    "",
    "**b)** lim ln x / (1/x) = lim (1/x) / (-1/x²) = -x = 0",
    "",
    "**c)** lim (e^x)/(2x) = ∞",
    "",
    "**d)** lim (2 e^{2x})/1 = 0",
    "",
    "**e)** lim (1)/(k e^{kx}) = 0",
    "",
    "### Exercise 9: L'Hôpital's Rule - Indeterminate Differences",
    "",
    "**a)** lim (√(x² + x) - x) = lim (x² + x - x²)/(√(x² + x) + x) = lim (x)/(√(x² + x) + x) = lim x / (x √(1 + 1/x) + x) = lim 1 / (√(1 + 1/x) + 1) = 1/2",
    "",
